FBIS4-18776 "drweu069_j_94008" FBIS-WEU-94-069 Daily Report 10 Apr 1994 ITALY & VATICAN CITY Tehran, Rome Hold Talks on Debt Rescheduling Tehran, Rome Hold Talks on Debt Rescheduling LD1004133694 Tehran IRNA in English 1213 GMT 10 Apr 94 LD1004133694 Tehran IRNA English BFN [Text] Rome, April, 10, IRNA -- Iran and Italy are now engaged in financial negotiations focusing on rescheduling Iran's debts to Italian firms, Iran's ambassador here, Majid Hedayat-Zadeh Razawi said Saturday [9 April]. Razawi told IRNA that Italy is Iran's third largest trade partner and Iran is Italy's third largest supplier of crude oil with trade between the two countries standing at drls. 3 billion annually. The issue can be settled if Italian creditor companies agree to reschedule the debts owed by Iran to them in a way that Iran can pay off its debts in a four year period starting two years after such an agreement is reached, he said. "As a matter of fact, no figure has been mentioned in the negotiations or in a letter of understanding inked by the two countries.... What is important is the topic of discussion and an overall agreement," he said.
